    com.poesys.bs.delegate.IDataDelegate<BsParty,IParty,com.poesys.db.pk.SequencePrimaryKey>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PartyDelegate

    public abstract class AbstractPartyDelegate
extends com.poesys.bs.delegate.AbstractDataDelegate<BsParty,IParty,com.poesys.db.pk.SequencePrimaryKey>

    A business delegate that provides an application programming interface for Party objects and their dependents. You should not modify this class; instead, override or add methods in the class PartyDelegate, which specializes this class.

    An abstract entity that is either a person or an organization

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
    See Also:
    PartyDelegate

      • createParty

        public BsParty createParty(java.math.BigInteger partyId,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  java.lang.String partyType)
                    throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException

        Create a new Party with data fields.

        The Party class has a sequence key; this method generates the sequence for later insertion into the database.

        Parameters:
        partyId - primary key attribute
        name - the name by which the party is known
        partyType - the kind of Party this is: User
        Returns:
        the new Party object
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when there is a problem generating the key or creating the object

      • createIpRange

        public BsIpRange createIpRange(BsParty parent,
                      java.math.BigInteger partyId,
                      java.lang.String start,
                      java.lang.String end)
                        throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException
        Create a new IpRange child of Party with a composite key.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent of the child object to create
        partyId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        start - the IP address that is the first address in the range; must not be part of any other range for the subscription
        end - the IP address that is the last address in the range; must be greater than the start and must be a "reasonable" end to the range (TBD)
        Returns:
        a new IpRange business layer DTO
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when a parameter causes a problem

      • createLogin

        public BsLogin createLogin(BsParty parent,
                  java.math.BigInteger partyId,
                  java.lang.String username,
                  java.lang.String password,
                  java.lang.String email,
                  java.lang.String institution,
                  java.lang.String userIdentifier,
                  java.math.BigInteger partnerId)
                    throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException
        Create a new Login child of Party with a composite key.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent of the child object to create
        partyId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        username - the unique, case-insensitive username for a party
        password - the password that authenticates the user/party
        email - the party's email address
        institution - the name of the organization to which the party belongs, such as a company or university name
        userIdentifier - a partner-specific identifier for the user, represented as a string (such as the TAIR community id); used by the partner to identify the user
        partnerId - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
        Returns:
        a new Login business layer DTO
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when a parameter causes a problem

                                                      java.util.UUID activationCodeId)
                                                        throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException
        Create a new SubscriptionTransaction child of Subscription with a composite key.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent of the child object to create
        partnerId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        partyId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        transactionNo - the identifying transaction number within the subscription that uniquely identifies the transaction along with the subscription key
        transactionDate - the date and time of the transaction
        startDate - at the time of the transaction, the date at which the subscription commences
        endDate - at the time of the transaction, the date at which the subscription ends
        transactionType - the kind of transaction: Initial, Renewal, Refund
        activationCodeId - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
        Returns:
        a new SubscriptionTransaction business layer DTO
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when a parameter causes a problem

                                java.lang.Long subscriptionId)
                                  throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException
        Create a new Subscription association class child of Party with an association key. This class links the input objects.
        Parameters:
        subscribedPartnersObject - associated Partner object (part of the key)
        subscribersObject - associated Party object (part of the key)
        partnerId - Attribute that is part of the association key
        partyId - Attribute that is part of the association key
        startDate - the date and time at which the subscription commences; if this is in the future, the subscription is not yet in effect
        endDate - the date and time at which the subscription ends
        subscriptionId - an alternate single-number identifier for the subscription
        Returns:
        a new Subscription business layer DTO
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when a parameter causes a problem
